HEADWORD: Demicircle
<hw>Dem"i*cir`cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>demi-cercle</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for measuring angles,
in surveying, etc. It resembles a protractor, but has an alidade,
sights, and a compass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

